5 583 M
(SC22 for development.) s
5 561 M
(1. Title) s
5 539 M
(Technical Report on C++ Performance) s
5 517 M
(2. Scope) s
5 495 M
(A Technical Report regarding the performance of C++ code executing) s
5 484 M
(in environments with limited resources.) s
5 462 M
(The report will have these sections:) s
5 440 M
( * Preamble) s
5 429 M
( * A Guide for Users) s
5 418 M
( * A Guide for Implementors) s
5 407 M
( * Programmer-directed Optimizations) s
5 396 M
( * Library Extensions) s
5 374 M
(Possible areas of coverage for each of those sections may include:) s
5 352 M
(Preamble) s
5 341 M
(-- Definition of terminology and scope of the report) s
5 330 M
(-- Description of potential resource limitations) s
5 319 M
(-- Kinds of problems often encountered in resource-limited environments) s
5 297 M
(A Guide for Users) s
5 286 M
(-- Assuming all features are available, routes for performance) s
5 275 M
(   improvement) s
5 264 M
(-- Information from the EC++ style guide as starting point) s
5 242 M
(A Guide for Implementors) s
5 231 M
(-- Performance effects of language features and combinations thereof) s
5 220 M
(-- Performance effects of library features and combinations thereof) s
5 209 M
(-- Basic I/O hardware addressing \(JTC 1/SC22 N2767\)) s
5 198 M
(-- ROMability) s
5 187 M
(-- Definition of volatile) s
5 176 M
(-- Performance guarantees) s
5 154 M
(Programmer-directed Optimizations) s
5 143 M
(-- Transforming virtual calls into non-virtual calls) s
5 132 M
(-- Alternatives to exception handling) s
5 121 M
(-- Effects of restrictions upon character types) s
5 110 M
(-- Characterization of performance guarantees) s
5 88 M
(Library Extensions) s
5 77 M
(-- Low-level storage allocation in operator new) s
5 66 M
(-- Basic I/O hardware addressing \(JTC 1/SC22 N2767\)) s
5 55 M
(-- Fixed-size data types \(as in C9X's <stdint.h>\)) s
5 22 M
